{"title": "Justified Criminal", "content": "This is a trope for when a person becomes a criminal because of socio-economic reasons, or just plain horrible circumstances, and is portrayed sympathetically because of this. Basically a person or a group of people are in dire straits and need money immediately and become bank robbers and drug dealers out of necessity. This trope usually occurs in crime dramas (specifically urban dramas). Also may be considered Truth in Television. And more often than not it's usually overlapped with Plethora of Mistakes. Also can be a case where a hero has to choose to do what's right despite being illegal. Or something morally dubious for a greater good. This trope almost always falls on the Gray and Grey Morality side.\n\nSome social analysts have also have been known to refer to this as \"Survival Crimes\".\n\nThis trope is to be expected in a Crapsack World. See also Karmic Thief and Caper Rationalization. Compare to: I Did What I Had to Do. See also Single Mom Stripper, in which necessity leads to degrading (but not necessarily criminal) work, Healthcare Motivation, in which the criminal wants money to pay a treatment or operation for a friend or sibling, Trapped by Gambling Debts for when the criminal is attempting to pay off debts, and The Commies Made Me Do It for people Forced into Evil by those holding their loved ones hostage.\n\nMay involve an Asshole Victim on the receiving end, particularly if the Justified Criminal is presented as sympathetic for committing assault or even murder in the defense of someone else. The most justified examples also steal for survival and non-violently.\n\nSee also Jaywalking Will Ruin Your Life, for when the crime that started it all was pathetic, but still more than enough to cast one out of civilized society.\n\nCompare Well-Intentioned Extremist and Your Terrorists Are Our Freedom Fighters for more politically-flavored sister-tropes.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/JustifiedCriminal?from=Main.SympatheticCriminal", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SpiderMan3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/PuellaMagiMadokaMagica", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/FullmetalAlchemist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/Naruto", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/DeathNote", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MagicalGirlLyricalNanohaAs", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheJoker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/WillEisner", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/OliverTwist", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/ThePro", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/Aladdin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Disney/AladdinAndTheKingOfThieves", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BatmanBegins", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SpiderMan3", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/SpiderManHomecoming", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/GoneInSixtySeconds2000", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DeadPresidents", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/VForVendetta", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/FunWithDickAndJane", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CatchThatKid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DogDayAfternoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/JohnQ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/SamuelLJackson", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheNegotiator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/CatchMeIfYouCan", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/SergioLeone", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheGoodTheBadAndTheUgly", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/OnceUponATimeInTheWest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DuckYouSucker", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Armored", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheShowMustGoOn2007", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Deewaar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/LesMiserables", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheTimeTravelersWife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WorldWarZ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/HollowPlaces", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/MaximumRide", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/OnTheRun", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/DarkLife", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheMillenniumTrilogy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/PleaseDontTellMyParentsImASupervillain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Relativity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/CityOfBones1995", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/